@@ -0,0 +1,115 @@
+# Implementation Notes
+
+Does not support manual control of visibility since I don't know how to enforce the correct accessibility implementation.
+The developer must implement it themselves.
+
+- MenuBar
+- DropdownMenu
+- Nested/Cascading Dropdown Menu
+- Context Menu
+  - Can be nested/cascading as well
+
+## MenuButton
+
+- `Space`, `Enter`, and `ArrowDown` opens menu and focuses first element
+- `ArrowUp` opens menu and focuses last element
+- Clicking the `MenuToggle` should toggle the visibility
+
+## MenuItemButton
+
+- used in `Menu` for nested dropdown menus or in a `MenuBar`
+- Clicking the `MenuToggle` should toggle the visibility without closing any parent menus (Nested Dropdown Menus only)
+- Horizontal:
+  - `Space`, `Enter`, and `ArrowDown` opens menu and focuses first element
+  - `ArrowUp` opens menu and focuses last element
+- Vertical:
+  - `Space`, `Enter`, and `ArrowRight` opens menu and focuses first element
+  - `ArrowLeft` opens menu and focuses last element
+
+## Menu
+
+- should be fixed to the MenuToggle
+- when the menu closes, the MenuToggle should be refocused unless:
+  - a MenuItemLink was clicked (links generally move focus themselves)
+  - the menu was closed because the menu is no longer visible in the viewport (scroll and resize events)
+- Escape closes menu
+- Horizontal:
+  - Home, End, ArrowDown, ArrowUp, and typing moves focus
+  - Arrow Right opens nested menus
+  - Arrow left closes nested menus
+- Vertical
+  - Home, End, ArrowLeft, ArrowRight, and typing moves focus
+  - ArrowDown opens nested menus
+  - ArrowUp closes nested menus
+- should close on any click event.
+  - close behavior can be disabled by calling event.stopPropagation() on any element
+- should probably be controlled with:
+  - visible
+  - onRequestClose
+  - should `onRequestClose` just be called hide/close? (global change since it applies to dialogs and sheets as well)
+- might have to make this controlled for the keyboard movement behavior as well. A temporary listbox is pretty much the same as a Menu, but movement is handled virtually.
+  - Listbox is used by Select and AutoComplete
+  - if I integrate Listbox behavior into a Menu, a `Listbox` should probably be updated to be the inline version of moving between two groups...
+    - probably not worth the effort because of mobile. I could mimic what we do at work, but.. trying to customize that is a pain
+    - it looks like if I implement the dual listbox thing, it requires a separator before and after describing the region
+  - Reminder: `<optgroup>` is implemented as:
+    ```tsx
+    <List role="group" aria-labelledby="label-id">
+      <ListItem id="label-id" role="presentation">
+        Group
+      </ListItem>
+      <Option>Label</Option>
+    </List>
+    ```
+
+## ContextMenu
+
+- might not be needed. Must be controlled and activated via context menus:
+  - right click on mouse
+  - long tap for touch devices
+
+## MenuSheet
+
+- a sheet that renders a menu
+- focus should default to the menu and use that menu's focus behavior
+- can be configured to have a header and footer which can become default focus instead
+- tabbing should switch between elements in the header, the menu, and then elements in the footer
+
+## Dropdown Menu
+
+- implements a combination of a Menu + MenuToggle
+- a MenuToggle is either a MenuButton or MenuItemButton depending on context
+- Other behavior:
+  - Click events should automatically close the menu unless event.stopPropagation() is called
+- Conditionally controlled. It will need both `visible` and `setVisible` though
+- Or maybe just add a `ControlledDropdownMenu` that is always controlled and requires a user to pass the implementation?
+- How much do users really need to control the menu visibility? I can really only think of setting it visible because of another action, but... seems bad UX?
+
+## MenuBar
+
+- roving tab index
+- renders as a List
+- horizontal by default
+- renders all menu toggles as MenuItem instead of a Button
+- this is what allows for the "hover mode" for menus
+- Hover Mode:
+  - disables transitions while active
+  - nested menus inherit the same hover timeout
+  - `hoverTimeout`:
+    - `undefined` - requires a click before it is enabled
+    - `-1` - never enabled
+    - `0` - always enabled
+    - any other positive number - number of ms of hovering before enabling
+- keyboard movement:
+  - roving tab index
+  - Horizontal:
+    - Home, End, ArrowLeft, ArrowRight, and typing moves focus
+    - ArrowDown opens menus
+    - ArrowUp closes menus
+  - Vertical
+    - Home, End, ArrowUp, ArrowDown, and typing moves focus
+    - ArrowRight opens menus
+    - ArrowLeft closes menus
+  - while a `Menu` is visible:
+    - ArrowLeft/ArrowRight should hide current menu, move focuses to next menu toggle, and open menu
+    - the menu should not focus a MenuItem once it becomes visible. ArrowDown or ArrowUp are required to move focus into the menu
